# Billing

CSA Admin aims to automate most tasks related to billing ([memberships](#memberships), [share capital](#share-capital), [payment processing](#payments)), but some aspects such as billing for [uncompleted <%= activities_human_name %>](#activity) must be done manually.

## Invoice types {#invoice-types}

CSA Admin handles several types of invoices:

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Membership** | Main subscription billing (<%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %>, <%= BasketComplement.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %>, depot, delivery cycle). [Automatically generated](#memberships). |
| **Annual fee** | Included in the first membership invoice, or [billed separately](#annual-fee) for [support members](/handbook/members#statuses). |
| **Share capital** | For organizations requiring [share ownership](#share-capital). Automatically generated when shares are missing. |
| **<%= activities_human_name %>** | Billing for [uncompleted participations](#activity). Triggered manually or in group. |
| **Shop order** | Invoice for [shop](/handbook/shop) orders. Can be automatic or manual. |
| **New member fee** | One-time fee charged to new members, if the feature is enabled. |
| **Other** | [Free-form invoices](#manual-invoice) for miscellaneous items or services. |

<!-- country:CH -->
## QR-Invoices {#qr-invoices}

CSA Admin generates QR-invoices with reference numbers (PDF) and sends them to all emails of the concerned member.

### QR-IBAN {#qr-iban}

To generate these invoices, you need a **QR-IBAN** from your bank. This is a special IBAN (starting with CH and containing 30 or 31 as the bank clearing number) that is different from your regular bank account IBAN. Only the QR-IBAN allows generating Swiss QR-invoices with reference numbers — a normal IBAN is not supported for this purpose.

You can request a QR-IBAN from your bank and then enter it in [your invoice settings](/settings#invoice).

> If you're unsure whether you already have a QR-IBAN, try entering it in [your invoice settings](/settings#invoice) — the system will validate its format and reject it if it's not a valid QR-IBAN. If you don't have one, request it from your bank.
<!-- /country:CH -->

## Memberships {#memberships}

Membership billing is completely automated by the system. You can define in [the settings (Automatic billing)](/settings#billing) the day of the week when the system will review all memberships and automatically create and send necessary invoices.

It is therefore crucial that each membership configuration is up to date so that invoices are correct.

### Recurring automatic billing {#recurring-billing}

Recurring billing is the mechanism that handles membership invoicing. It must be enabled for any membership invoice to be created; without it, no membership invoices are generated or sent at all.

#### How to enable it

In [the settings (Automatic billing)](/settings#billing), choose the **day of the week** on which the system should run. Every week on that day, the system reviews all members and creates invoices when due. Invoices created this way are **automatically sent** by email.

> It is advisable to choose a day other than the delivery day. This way, any membership or basket changes made on the delivery day are reflected in the invoice generated in the following days, rather than being invoiced prematurely the same day or waiting a full week.

#### Payment intervals {#billing-year-divisions}

Each membership has a **payment interval** (also called billing year division) that determines how many invoices are generated over the fiscal year. The available intervals are configured in [the settings](/settings#billing) and offered to members during registration or renewal.

Available intervals: Annual (1), Semi-annual (2), Four-monthly (3), Quarterly (4), Monthly (12).

The invoice amount is calculated as: **total membership amount ÷ number of remaining intervals**. For example, for a 1000.- membership paid quarterly, each invoice will be 250.-.

#### When is the first invoice sent? {#first-invoice-timing}

By default, the first invoice is sent on the billing day following the **first <%= Basket.model_name.human.downcase %> delivery**. This means no invoice is generated before the member has received their first delivery.

This behavior can be changed in [the settings](/settings#billing) by disabling "Bill memberships only after their first delivery". When disabled, billing starts from the **membership start date**, even before any delivery.

#### When does billing end? {#billing-end}

By default, billing extends until the **membership end date**, covering the full fiscal year even if there are no deliveries in the last months.

This can be changed in [the settings](/settings#billing) by enabling "Bill memberships until their last delivery only". When enabled, billing only covers up to the month of the last delivery. This is useful when the last months of the fiscal year have no deliveries.

#### Detailed logic

Each billing day, the system checks every member and determines whether an invoice is due:

1. The fiscal year is divided into periods based on the payment interval (e.g. quarterly = 4 periods of 3 months).
2. If the **current period has already been billed**, the next invoice is scheduled for the beginning of the next period.
3. If the **current period has not been billed yet**, the invoice is created on the next billing day, respecting the "first delivery" or "membership start" setting described above.
4. If the calculated next invoice date falls **after the fiscal year end**, no further invoice is generated for this year.

The invoice is always created on the configured day of the week. If an invoice becomes due on a different day (e.g. a new period starts on a Wednesday but billing day is Monday), it will be created the following Monday.

#### Next invoice date

From a member's or membership's page, the "Billing" section (right column) displays the **next invoice date**. This shows when the next automatic invoice will be created and sent.

This date updates dynamically: once an invoice is sent, it moves to the next scheduled date.

### Bill now {#bill-now}

In some cases, for example after a change in membership configuration, you may want to create an invoice immediately rather than waiting for the next billing day. To do this, click on the "Bill now" button in the "Billing" section (right column) of the member's or membership's page.

The invoice will be created but **not sent**. You can consult the PDF and send it manually using the "Send" button on its page. This is useful if you're in contact with a member and want to quickly rectify an invoice or verify the result of a configuration change.

> The "Bill now" button produces the exact same invoice as the automatic system would, the only difference is that it's not sent automatically, giving you a chance to review it first.

### Invoice all in advance {#future_billing}

It is possible to invoice an upcoming subscription in advance, with a start date in the future, whether it is in the current fiscal year or the next fiscal year. Subscriptions invoiced in this way are fully invoiced at once, regardless of the payment interval configured for the subscription.

Advance invoicing can be done from the page of a future subscription by clicking on the "Invoice all in advance" button in the "Billing" section (right column). It is also possible to invoice multiple future subscriptions at once from [the subscriptions page](/memberships?scope=future&q[during_year]=<%= Current.fy_year + 1 %>), using the "Future" field and filtering by fiscal year. You can then click on the "Invoice all in advance" button in the "Billing" section (right column), below the filters. Feel free to filter future subscriptions by payment interval (e.g., "Annual" only) to refine your selection.

> The annual fee corresponding to the fiscal year of the subscription is automatically included in the invoice.

### Price change {#price-change}

If a membership configuration (dates, <%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %>, ...) is modified, several cases are possible:

- A future invoice still needs to be sent (it's the middle of the year and the member is billed each quarter); in this case, the price change (positive or negative) will simply be applied to the next invoice.
- The last invoice has already been sent (it's the end of the year or the member is billed once), there are then 2 possibilities:
  - The price change is positive, a new invoice (with a higher amount) will simply be created on the next billing day to bill the missing amount.
  - The price change is negative, the last invoice(s) of the membership will then be automatically cancelled and a new invoice (with a lower amount) will be recreated on the next billing day. If the old cancelled invoice was already paid, then the new invoice will be automatically closed and the member will end up with a positive balance. If needed, you can reflect a refund of the member's balance by [creating a negative payment](/payments/new) for them.

### Annual fee {#annual-fee}

When the annual fee feature is enabled, the organization's default annual fee is defined in [the annual fee settings](/settings#annual_fee). Each member inherits this default when created, but it can be overridden individually from their profile (edit page, "Billing" section).

When enabled, the annual fee is automatically included in the **first invoice** of the membership. If the member doesn't have a membership ([support](/handbook/members#statuses)), a specific annual fee invoice is automatically created at the beginning of the fiscal year.

If you change the organization's default annual fee, all members still set to the previous value are automatically updated to the new one.

### Trial <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> {#trial-baskets}

If a number of trial <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> is defined in [the billing settings](/settings#billing), then the membership will only be billed once all trial <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> are delivered, on the next billing day following the delivery of the first non-trial <%= Basket.model_name.human.downcase %>. This ensures the first invoice is not generated while the member can still cancel their trial membership themselves.

Members can cancel their membership themselves during the trial period from their member account. The membership will then end on the last trial <%= Basket.model_name.human.downcase %> delivery date. To cancel a membership immediately, the admin must do so manually.

If the membership is canceled during the trial period, only the delivered <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> will be billed, on the next billing day. In this case, the annual fee is not billed (unless the member chooses to pay it).

### <%= Member.human_attribute_name(:salary_basket) %>

Members flagged as "[<%= Member.human_attribute_name(:salary_basket).downcase %>](/handbook/members#salary-basket)" are completely excluded from billing. Their membership still exists for delivery tracking, but all prices are zeroed out and no membership invoices are generated.

## Share capital {#share-capital}

When the cooperative shares feature is enabled, the price per share and the default number of required shares are defined in [the cooperative shares settings](/settings#shares). The required number of shares can also be set per <%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %> (e.g., a larger size may require more shares).

When the feature is enabled, each billing day the system automatically creates invoices for missing share capital, for example for a member whose membership has just started.

### Member share fields {#share-fields}

Three share-related fields are available on a member's profile (edit page, "Billing" section):

- **Number of existing share capital**: Shares already owned outside of CSA Admin (e.g., from a previous system). These are not billed again.
- **Desired number of share capital**: Members can request additional shares beyond the minimum during [registration](/handbook/registration) or [renewal](/handbook/membership_renewal). The system invoices the higher of the required and desired amounts.
- **Number of required share capital**: Admin override for the number of shares this member needs. Defaults to the value configured for their <%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %>.

### Refund {#share-refund}

To refund already billed share capital, go to the invoice page and click on the "Refund" button at the top right, you can then easily create a negative share capital invoice. Make sure that the member no longer needs share capital, otherwise they will be automatically created again on the next billing day.

> From a member's page, you can see in the "Billing" section (right column) the number of share capital that will be or are already billed with a link to the corresponding invoices.

## Uncompleted <%= activities_human_name %> {#activity}

Each organization has a different billing policy for uncompleted <%= activities_human_name.downcase %>, some bill them, others don't.
CSA Admin allows you to bill uncompleted <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> individually or in groups.

### Defining members to bill

The total of uncompleted <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> is displayed on [the dashboard](/dashboard). For more details, you can export the CSV [of memberships](/memberships) for the concerned fiscal year. The "<%= activities_human_name %> missing" column is available specifically for this.
By opening the CSV with Excel, it's easy to determine the members to bill by sorting them using this column. If necessary, you can then adjust the number of <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> requested for each member by directly modifying their membership (field: "<%= activities_human_name %> (full year)").

### Individual billing

Either using the "Bill" button from a rejected participation page or from [the new invoice creation page](/invoices/new). Simply enter the number of <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> to bill and click on the "Create Invoice" button.

Don't forget to send the invoice, it's not sent automatically so you can check it.

### Group billing

From [the participations page](/activity_participations), below the filters, a "Billing" section allows you to bill all missing participations for a specific year in one click. ✨

Invoices are automatically sent here.

### Content of [the "New invoice" email](/mail_templates/invoice_created) {#activity-email}

It's possible to add specific text in the ["New invoice" email template](/mail_templates/invoice_created) for <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> invoices using [Liquid syntax](https://shopify.github.io/liquid) as follows:

~~~ liquid
{% case invoice.entity_type %}
  {% when 'ActivityParticipation' %}
    <p>My special text!</p>
  {% else %}
    <p>My standard text.</p>
{% endcase %}
~~~

## Manual invoice (Other) {#manual-invoice}

CSA Admin offers the possibility to manually bill various items or services (for example, purchase of fabric bags for new subscribers). To do this, simply [create a new invoice](/invoices/new) and enter the items under the "Other" tab. After checking the PDF, you can manually send the invoice using the "Send" button on its page.

> Attention, "Other" type invoices should not be used to bill memberships, share capital or <%= activities_human_name.downcase %>, as the system will not take them into account.

## VAT {#vat}

If your organization is subject to VAT, enable the VAT feature and configure your VAT number and rates in [the VAT settings](/settings#vat). Separate rates can be defined for membership invoices, <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> invoices, and shop order invoices. For "Other" and "New member fee" invoices, the VAT rate is set manually on each invoice.

VAT is calculated as an inclusive tax (the invoice total already includes VAT). The net amount and VAT amount are displayed separately on the invoice PDF.

> VAT is only applied when the VAT feature is enabled. The VAT settings require a VAT number and a membership VAT rate; <%= activities_human_name.downcase %> and shop VAT rates are optional and only used when those features are enabled.

## Payments {#payments}

Each time a payment is created (automatically or manually) or an invoice is created or cancelled, the system will distribute the amount of all payments to existing invoices in the following priority order:

1. Payment with reference number, redistribution until the referenced invoice is closed.
2. Redistribution of payments without reference number and excess amounts to invoices that were previously already marked as closed in chronological order.
3. Redistribution of payments without reference number and excess amounts to still open invoices in chronological order, the oldest invoices are closed first.

This redistribution mode is very convenient and thus allows managing cases where a member would reuse an old reference number to pay a new invoice.

### Automatic import {#automatic_payments_processing}

The most efficient way to process your payments is to ask your bank to set up [an EBICS connection](https://www.six-group.com/en/products-services/banking-services/standardization.html#scrollTo=ebics). This allows the system to automatically import (each night) payments of invoices with reference numbers from your members via the ISO camt.054 format.

<!-- country:CH -->
CSA Admin also manages automatic retrieval of payments from the [Alternative Bank Switzerland (ABS)](https://www.abs.ch/en) which doesn't support the EBICS system.
<!-- /country:CH -->

> If you have questions about support for a particular bank or setting up EBICS, don't hesitate to [ask me](/support).

### Setting up EBICS {#ebics-setup}

Setting up an EBICS connection with your bank involves several steps and typically takes a few days. Here is the process:

1. **Request the EBICS registration form from your bank** — Contact your bank to ask them to activate an EBICS connection for your account with daily fetch and **camt.054** file support.
2. **Send me the bank document** — Following your registration request, you will receive a document from your bank (containing the Participant ID, etc.), scan it and [send it to me](/support).
3. **INI letter signing** — I will initialize the connection and send you back an INI letter. You must sign **pages 1 and 3** and send it to your bank.
4. **Finalization** — Once your bank has received and validated the signed INI letter, I can finalize the connection.

> In the meantime, you can use [manual import](#manual-import) to process your payments.

<!-- country:CH -->
### Setting up Alternative Bank Switzerland (ABS) {#abs-setup}

The connection with [Alternative Bank Switzerland (ABS)](https://www.abs.ch/en) uses a keyfile (key file) system, as it doesn't support EBICS. Here is the process:

1. **Contact the bank** — Via your secure e-banking messaging channel, request a "keyfile (key file) connection" for your existing e-banking contract (IBXXXXXXX).
2. **Receive the keyfile** — The bank will send you an encrypted keyfile (`.p12` format) by email and its password by separate post mail.
3. **Send me the information** — Once you have received all the details, please send them to me, ideally via a secure end-to-end encrypted channel (Signal, Telegram, WhatsApp, iMessage, ...):
   - The encrypted keyfile (`.p12` format) and its password
   - Your IBXXXXXXX contract number
   - Your IBXXXXXXX contract password, same as your e-banking password. Note that I cannot access your e-banking — the system can only fetch the camt.054 files containing the list of payments.
   - Your bank account number (XXX.XXX.XXX-XX)

> ⚠️ If you change your e-banking password or if your IB contract is removed, please let me know promptly — payment retrieval will stop working until the information is updated. If the IB contract is removed, the full setup will need to be restarted with a new contract.
<!-- /country:CH -->

### Manual import {#manual-import}

When automatic import via [EBICS](https://www.six-group.com/en/products-services/banking-services/standardization.html#scrollTo=ebics) is not yet configured, you can easily import payments of invoices with reference numbers from your members by downloading a file in camt.053, camt.054, or mt940 format from your e-banking and uploading it to CSA Admin from [the payments page](/payments), "Import" section in the right column. Don't forget to repeat the operation regularly (every week) until the automatic import is in place.

For payments without a reference number (cash or direct deposit), you simply need to [create a new payment manually](/payments/new). Its amount will be automatically redistributed to existing open invoices.

> Please try to only stick to a single format when importing payments, doing otherwise may lead to double payments creation.

### Refund

If you wish to refund a member for any reason, simply create a new payment with a negative amount. Note that the refund must be made by you from your e-banking for example, as CSA Admin cannot create a transfer.

